            "content": "<h2>Defining Lab Grown Diamonds </h2>",
            "custom_id": "defining"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_WMqYQp": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/LGD.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Lab Grown Diamond definition refers to the gemstones made by people, not nature. Also known as man-made or synthetic diamonds, they are grown under controlled lab conditions that mimic Earth’s natural process. While chemically, physically, structurally, and visually they share the same properties as the natural diamonds, the difference between the two boils down to their origin:</p><ul><li>Natural diamonds develop over millions of years under Earth’s heat and pressure.</li><li>Lab Grown Diamonds grow in labs within weeks through advanced technology.</li></ul><p>So, you get a beautiful, genuine, and real diamond that’s kinder to the planet and often easier on your budget.</p>",
